        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 2:35AM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 235 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Embry, or 7 miles northwest of Eupora, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eupora, Maben, Mathiston, Pheba, Walthall, Bellefontaine, Cumberland,
Reform, Sherwood, Embry, and Clarkson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
